The zonal leadership of the Peoples Democratic Party, (PDP), in the South West has described a meeting held at the behest of Governor Seyi Makinde as unconstitutional. Makinde and some leaders of the party in the southwest held a meeting in Ibadan on Friday where they resolved to build the party. Present at the meeting were former Governor Olugunsoye Oyinlola (Osun) ; former Governor Ayo Fayose (Ekiti); his predecessor, Chief Segun Oni; a former military administrator of Ondo State and former PDP deputy national chairman, Chief Olabode George, National Assembly members and other stakeholders of the party. However, the zonal leadership of the party in a statement signed by its publicity secretary, Ayo Fadaka, described the meeting as a mere gathering of friends of the Governor. He also stated that any resolution made at the meeting is not binding on the party in the south west noting that the meeting was held without any recourse to the zonal leadership.